               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>The scope of the EDC contract is to provide multi-disciplinary engineering and design services, and construction works that will enable the delivery of infrastructure and construction projects. The contract will provide EDC works and services including but not limited to:</P>
                  <P>— Construction: Civils, Groundworks, Piling, Building, Mechanical, Electrical, Control Systems, Asset Management, Landscaping and Security Enhancements,</P>
                  <P>— Professional Services and Engineering Services: Programme and Project Management, Design, Studies, Site Investigations and Surveys, Radiological, Environmental, Supervision of Works,</P>
                  <P>The scope of projects that may be delivered, include but are not limited to:</P>
                  <P>— cap perimeter drainage system including storage lagoon detailed,</P>
                  <P>— container ullage fill methodology and implementation of the works,</P>
                  <P>— import and stockpile of void filling material,</P>
                  <P>— void fill methodology (between containers) and implementation of void filling,</P>
                  <P>— installation of a running surface to enable higher stacking of containers,</P>
                  <P>— construction of a cut-off wall to the north and west of Vault 8,</P>
                  <P>— design and installation of Vault 8 leachate monitoring system,</P>
                  <P>— undertake observational monitoring of Vault 8, during higher stacking,</P>
                  <P>— installation of temporary drainage between Vault 8 and the trenches,</P>
                  <P>— repair of existing trench cap membranes,</P>
                  <P>— preparation of stockpile areas,</P>
                  <P>— placement of profile and surcharge material to trench cap (north) to enable necessary settlement,</P>
                  <P>— undertake observational monitoring of the trench cap settlement,</P>
                  <P>— installation of trench cap environmental monitoring system including groundwater monitoring wells and trench cap probe holes,</P>
                  <P>— placement of profile fill to Vault 8 utilising surcharge material,</P>
                  <P>— importation and management of materials,</P>
                  <P>— installation of a batching plant for engineered layers,</P>
                  <P>— installation of the engineered Final Cap over Vault 8 and the north end of the trenches,</P>
                  <P>— final landscaping,</P>
                  <P>The estimated total value of the requirements is in the range of 50 000 000 GBP to 80 000 000 GBP.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <INFO_ADD>
                  <P>Please note this is a PIN for the market engagement therefore the full scope of requirements is yet to be defined and as the procurement progresses the requirements may change.</P>
               </INFO_ADD>
